x = df.iloc[:,3:].values



     























Finding the WCSS(Within Cluster Sum of Squares) values using KMeans Clustering



















In [7]:



     


wcss = []
for i in range(2,11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i,init='k-means++')
    kmeans.fit(x)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
display(wcss)

plt.show()

In [10]:



     


kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=5,init='k-means++')
kmeans.fit(x)
y_kmeans = kmeans.labels_
display(y_kmeans)

Plotting the Scatter Plot Graph with the independent variable and the Cluster which it belongs and saving the PNG file



















In [11]:



     


plt.scatter(x[y_kmeans==0,0],x[y_kmeans==0,1],s=100,c='r',label='cluster 1')
plt.scatter(x[y_kmeans==1,0],x[y_kmeans==1,1],s=100,c='b',label='cluster 2')
plt.scatter(x[y_kmeans==2,0],x[y_kmeans==2,1],s=100,c='g',label='cluster 3')
plt.scatter(x[y_kmeans==3,0],x[y_kmeans==3,1],s=100,c='m',label='cluster 4')
plt.scatter(x[y_kmeans==4,0],x[y_kmeans==4,1],s=100,c='c',label='cluster 5')
plt.legend()
plt.title('KMeans Clustering Spread')
plt.savefig('KMeans Clustering Spread Graph.png')
plt.show()

dend = sch.dendrogram(sch.linkage(x,method='ward'))
plt.title('Dendrogram ward')
plt.xlabel('Customer')
plt.ylabel('ED')
plt.savefig('Dendogram Ward.png')
plt.show()

Plotting the Dendogram Graph using single method to find out the exact ideal number of cluster to be created using Agglomerative Clustering Model with single Linkage and saving the PNG file



















In [20]:



     


import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.cluster import hierarchy as sch
dendrogram = sch.dendrogram(sch.linkage(x, method='single'))

plt.title('Dendrogram single')
plt.xlabel('Customer')
plt.ylabel('ED')
plt.savefig('Dendogram Single.png')
plt.show()



     






















    
    



































Fitting the Agglomerative Clustering model with ideal number of clusters found from Dendogram using single method and predicting the dataset belonging to the cluster.
